      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">FORM OF RECOMMENDATION ¶ FOR A FELLOW OF THE LINNEAN SOCIETY OF LONDON ¶ . ¶ Professor James Bunyan Lillie Mackay, F.C.S. Director of the School of Mines Sandhurst, Australia ¶ a gentleman attached to...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.09.00b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Linnean Society of London</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Linnean Society, London, Certificates of Fellows, foreign members and associates, 1887-90.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <table n="Table1">
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">[Ass]<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                           <p rend="Footnote"
                              style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                              xml:lang="en">
                              <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                              <seg style="">
                                 <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS torn, here and below.</seg>
                           </p>
                        </note>ociate (late Scholar &amp; Exhibitioner) of King's College London</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">[Fe]llow of the Chemical Society of London</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">Member of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">Honary Secretary of the Bendigo Science Society – (170 members)</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">&amp;c&amp;c</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">Late Lecturer in Medical Botany &amp; Mater[ia Medica] Melbourne University ([…] </p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">Now Professor of Geology &amp; Mine[ralogy] and Director of the Sandhurst<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                           <p rend="Footnote"
                              style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                              xml:lang="en">
                              <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                              <seg style="">
                                 <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now Bendigo, Vic.</seg>
                           </p>
                        </note> School o[f Mines] Australia<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                           <p rend="Footnote"
                              style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                              xml:lang="en">
                              <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                              <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The body of the form appears to be in Mackay's hand (cf. the undated form of obligation that is filed with this certificate). The descriptive text above the printed heading of the form is smaller.</p>
                        </note>
                     </p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </table>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">FORM OF RECOMMENDATION</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">FOR A FELLOW OF THE LINNEAN SOCIETY OF LONDON</seg>
               <seg>.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">Professor James Bunyan Lillie Mackay, F.C.S. Director of the School of Mines Sandhurst, Australia</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">
                  <seg style="font-style: italic; ">a gentleman attached to the study of Natural History, especially</seg>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>Botany &amp; Geology <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">
                  <seg style="font-style: italic; ">being desirous of becoming a Fellow of the LINNEAN SOCIETY OF LONDON, we, whose names are underwritten, beg leave to recommend him to that honour.</seg>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <table n="Table2">
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">Robert Bentley</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">John Lubbock</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">George Henslow</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>[…]Brown<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                           <p rend="Footnote"
                              style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                              xml:lang="en">
                              <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                              <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The text of the forename or intials is indecipherable; There are three Fellows named Brown in the Fellows' List for 1888, of these the most likely is Robert Brown (1842-1895), then living in Streatham.</p>
                        </note>
                     </p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">Thos. Willshire</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
                        xml:lang="en">William Carruthers</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </table>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">
                  <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">This recommendation must be signed by Three or more Fellows.</seg>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">N.B. – The Christian name of the Candidate must be stated at length, as well as his Residence, and any special qualifications he may possess.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">This certificate was read at a General Meeting of the Society, on the</seg> 1st <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">day of</seg> Novbr. 1888.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>To have been read at the Society in November, the form must have been sent no later than September 1887, and it is numbered accordingly, although it was possible that it was sent earlier and arrived during the summer recess, i.e., after 21 June.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">The Ballot will take place on the</seg> 6th <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">day of</seg> Decbr., 1888<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated in pencil top left front above the missing section of the MS</seg>
                     <seg style="">: Materia Medica</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">top right in pencil</seg>
                     <seg style="">: Fees recd. from St[…]bridge at Brighton | Obl. recd 11/4/91. </seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; "> back, in ink: </seg>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Prof Jas Bunyan Lillie Mackay elected 6 Dec 1888.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
